## Language

- **Code and comments must be in English.** This includes:
  - Inline and block comments
  - Docstrings and JSDoc/TSDoc
  - Commit messages (when editing from this environment)
  - Variable, function, and type names (English, unless reflecting an external API or domain term)
  - User-facing strings in OQVA-specific files (e.g. env.oqva.example, run-oqva.sh help text, README additions)

- **Exception:** Existing upstream content in other languages (e.g. i18n, docs) may be left as-is when not modified.

## OQVA-specific files

- `docker-compose.oqva.yml`, `env.oqva.example`, `run-oqva.sh` and any new OQVA scripts or config: keep all comments and user-facing text in English.
